title: 'Memphis Madness' more low key than years past
text:
'Memphis Madness' more low key than years past Posted: canderson@wmctv.com MEMPHIS, TN (WMC) - 
The Memphis Tigers basketball team is taking a more understated approach to getting the fans ready for the season. 
No more Yo Gotti or Rick Ross concerts, but fans did get a chance to meet the players, watch the men's team take on the women's team in a 3-point contest, which was won by Ariel Hearn, and get pictures and autographs with the team. 
It's not the team that everyone expected, with Austin Nichols transferring during the summer, but the Tigers still think they have the talent it takes to improve on last season. 
The Tigers will test their mettle on Halloween, October 31st in a secret scrimmage against Georgia Tech.
